# Userspace C (einkd, tools)

Full guide: `docs/CODING_STYLE.md` · Architecture: `docs/ARCHITECTURE.md`

## Must follow

- **C throughout** — C11, no C++, no Rust in `userspace/`
- Same readability bar as kernel: names teach, short files/functions, sparse comments
- Plain C + POSIX/systemd: `sd-bus`, `hidraw`/`libevdev`, `syslog`/`sd_journal`
- Pixels via DRM only — no USB panel protocol in userspace
- SPDX headers; `-Wall -Wextra`; check all `malloc`/syscall returns
- Log failures with context: path, errno, mode name

## File layout (einkd)

Split by job: `main.c`, `dbus_api.c`, `hid_touch.c`, `mode_*.c` — not one mega `main.c`.

## Avoid

- GObject/C++ unless explicitly decided later (default: plain C)
- Cryptic names, obvious comments, duplicating kernel protocol code
